But didn’t we say not to do this?
• Okay to return a pointer to memory that is not managed by your scope
• NOT OKAY TO RETURN A POINTER TO A LOCAL VARIABLE (WHY?)
CMPSC 311 - Introduction to Systems Programming
int* max(int* a, int* b) {
  return (*a > *b) ? a : b;
}
void main(void) {
int x = 5, y = 6;
  printf("max of %d and %d is %d\n", x, y, *max(&x, &y));
}
int* foo(void) {
  int x = 5;
  return &x;
}
int main(void) {
  printf("%d\n", *foo());
}
REMEMBER: MALLOC MEMORY IS NOT STACK ALLOCATED, 
ITS ON THE HEAP (NOT YOUR “SCOPE”)!

