Filling memory
• memset fills n bytes of buf memory with a given constant byte value
void* memset(void* buf, unsigned char value, size_t n);

Returns the buffer that was passed in.
CMPSC 311 - Introduction to Systems Programming
char a[4] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
memset(a, 0, 4);
// what are the contents of a now?
int b[4] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
memset(b, 10, 4);
// what are the contents of b now? Be careful!

