Copying memory
• memcpy copies one memory region to another byte-wise
• Copy n bytes from src (“source”) buffer to dst (“destination”) buffer
char buf1[8] = { 'a', 'a', 'a', ‘a’, 'a', 'a', 'a', 'a' };
char buf2[4] = { 'b', 'b', 'b', 'b' };
memcpy(buf1, buf2, 4);
CMPSC 311 - Introduction to Systems Programming
