Dynamic Memory Deallocation
• To reap/release/free any dynamically allocated data, use free
• The passed pointer must point to the first byte of heap-allocated memory
• i.e., what previously returned by a malloc( ) or calloc( )
• Free does NOT work on statically or automatically allocated memory!*
• free(NULL) does nothing (for safety, we’ll talk about it)
• After freeing a block of memory, 
that block of memory can be used 
by some future malloc/calloc
• Enables memory reuse!
void free(void* ptr);
CMPSC 311 - Introduction to Systems Programming
// allocate a 10 element int array
int* arr = (int*)malloc(10 * sizeof(int));
if (arr == NULL) return -1;
arr[0] = 5;
// some more work / functions / returns...
// eventually when done...
free(arr);

